        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 25 at 3:51PM CDT by NWS Birmingham AL</headline>
        <description>At 350 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Vance, or 14 miles north of Centreville, moving northeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Tannehill Ironworks State Park, Abernant, Bucksville, Brookwood,
Weller, Vance, Woodstock, Marvel, Mercedes Benz Of Alabama, Green
Pond, Lake View, West Blocton, Caffee Junction, Hebron, I 20 Rest
Area Near Tuscaloosa, Cedar Cove, North Bibb, North Johns, and
Coaling.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
